        <MudText> The goal of this project was to experience and use a linux system as my main driver.</MudText>

        <MudText> For this purpose and for it just being a meme, I choose to use Arch Linux as my main OS.</MudText>



    <MudText>During the time I used Arch Linux, I tried out many of the various things it allows.</MudText>

    <MudText>For one I used various windows managers, however in the end I settled with a custom hyprland setup.
        I did try more desktop oriented environments like KDE, however I prefered the look and feel of hyprland more.
    </MudText>

    <MudText> However in the end I decided to switch back to mainly using Windows, as I used my Laptop most for software
        development.
        This would generally not be the issue, since I do prefer the feel of window managers. The problem however was
        that
        unity and similar systems, rarely support linux.
        This made it hard to work on projects as most would be very unstable.
    </MudText>

    <MudText> However I might consider switching back in the future, when I would be to find a workaround for this
        issue.
    </MudText>
